ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Rabbit hemorrhagic disease (RHD), also called Viral hemorrhagic diseases
(VHD) of rabbits, is a highly contagious and acute fatal disease of wild
and domestic European rabbits (_Oryctolagus cuniculus_), 1st reported in
1984 in the People's Republic of China. Currently, it is endemic in East
Asia, Europe (including the UK) and Oceania. Outbreaks have also been
recorded in Central America (Mexico and Cuba), USA, Saudi Arabia, West and
North Africa. The disease is one (B353) of the 3 lagomorph diseases
reportable to the OIE.
For further information, see moderator's commentary in postings
20050116.0132, 20040805.2145. - Mod.AS]
